18// Helper functions for extracting fields from encoded instructions.
19// InsnType must either be integral or an APInt-like object that must:
20// * Have a static const max_size_in_bits equal to the number of bits in the
21// encoding.
22// * be default-constructible and copy-constructible
23// * be constructible from a uint64_t
24// * be constructible from an APInt (this can be private)
25// * Support getBitsSet(loBit, hiBit)
26// * be convertible to uint64_t
27// * Support the ~, &, ==, !=, and |= operators with other objects of the same type
28// * Support shift (<<, >>) with signed and unsigned integers on the RHS
29// * Support put (<<) to raw_ostream&
30template <typename InsnType>
31#if defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__)
32__declspec(noinline)
33#endif
34static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
35 unsigned numBits, std::true_type) {
36 assert(startBit + numBits <= 64 && "Cannot support >64-bit extractions!");
37 assert(startBit + numBits <= (sizeof(InsnType) * 8) &&
38 "Instruction field out of bounds!");
39 InsnType fieldMask;
40 if (numBits == sizeof(InsnType) * 8)
41 fieldMask = (InsnType)(-1LL);
42 else
43 fieldMask = (((InsnType)1 << numBits) - 1) << startBit;
44 return (insn & fieldMask) >> startBit;
45}
46
47template <typename InsnType>
48static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
49 unsigned numBits, std::false_type) {
50 assert(startBit + numBits <= InsnType::max_size_in_bits && "Instruction field out of bounds!");
51 InsnType fieldMask = InsnType::getBitsSet(0, numBits);
52 return (insn >> startBit) & fieldMask;
53}
54
55template <typename InsnType>
56static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
57 unsigned numBits) {
58 return fieldFromInstruction(insn, startBit, numBits, std::is_integral<InsnType>());
59}

7996
7997template <typename InsnType>
7998static DecodeStatus decodeInstruction(const uint8_t DecodeTable[], MCInst &MI,
7999 InsnType insn, uint64_t Address,
8000 const void *DisAsm,
8001 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI) {
8002 const FeatureBitset &Bits = STI.getFeatureBits();
8003
8004 const uint8_t *Ptr = DecodeTable;
8005 InsnType CurFieldValue = 0;
8006 DecodeStatus S = MCDisassembler::Success;
8007 while (true) {
8008 ptrdiff_t Loc = Ptr - DecodeTable;
8009 switch (*Ptr) {
8010 default:
8011 errs() << Loc << ": Unexpected decode table opcode!\n";
8012 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
8013 case MCD::OPC_ExtractField: {
8014 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
8015 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
8016 ++Ptr;
8017 CurFieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
8018 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_ExtractField(" << Start << ", "
8019 << Len << "): " << CurFieldValue << "\n");
8020 break;
8021 }
8022 case MCD::OPC_FilterValue: {
8023 // Decode the field value.
8024 unsigned Len;
8025 InsnType Val = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8026 Ptr += Len;
8027 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
8028 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
8029 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
8030 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
8031
8032 // Perform the filter operation.
8033 if (Val != CurFieldValue)
8034 Ptr += NumToSkip;
8035 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_FilterValue(" << Val << ", " << NumToSkip
8036 << "): " << ((Val != CurFieldValue) ? "FAIL:" : "PASS:")
8037 << " continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
8038
8039 break;
8040 }
8041 case MCD::OPC_CheckField: {
8042 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
8043 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
8044 InsnType FieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
8045 // Decode the field value.
8046 InsnType ExpectedValue = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8047 Ptr += Len;
8048 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
8049 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
8050 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
8051 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
8052
8053 // If the actual and expected values don't match, skip.
8054 if (ExpectedValue != FieldValue)
8055 Ptr += NumToSkip;
8056 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckField(" << Start << ", "
8057 << Len << ", " << ExpectedValue << ", " << NumToSkip
8058 << "): FieldValue = " << FieldValue << ", ExpectedValue = "
8059 << ExpectedValue << ": "
8060 << ((ExpectedValue == FieldValue) ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
8061 break;
8062 }
8063 case MCD::OPC_CheckPredicate: {
8064 unsigned Len;
8065 // Decode the Predicate Index value.
8066 unsigned PIdx = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8067 Ptr += Len;
8068 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
8069 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
8070 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
8071 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
8072 // Check the predicate.
8073 bool Pred;
8074 if (!(Pred = checkDecoderPredicate(PIdx, Bits)))
8075 Ptr += NumToSkip;
8076 (void)Pred;
8077 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckPredicate(" << PIdx << "): "
8078 << (Pred ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
8079
8080 break;
8081 }
8082 case MCD::OPC_Decode: {
8083 unsigned Len;
8084 // Decode the Opcode value.
8085 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8086 Ptr += Len;
8087 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
8088 Ptr += Len;
8089
8090 MI.clear();
8091 MI.setOpcode(Opc);
8092 bool DecodeComplete;
8093 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, MI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
8094 assert(DecodeComplete);
8095
8096 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Decode: opcode " << Opc
8097 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": "
8098 << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
8099 return S;
8100 }
8101 case MCD::OPC_TryDecode: {
8102 unsigned Len;
8103 // Decode the Opcode value.
8104 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8105 Ptr += Len;
8106 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
8107 Ptr += Len;
8108 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
8109 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
8110 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
8111 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
8112
8113 // Perform the decode operation.
8114 MCInst TmpMI;
8115 TmpMI.setOpcode(Opc);
8116 bool DecodeComplete;
8117 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, TmpMI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
8118 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_TryDecode: opcode " << Opc
8119 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": ");
8120
8121 if (DecodeComplete) {
8122 // Decoding complete.
8123 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
8124 MI = TmpMI;
8125 return S;
8126 } else {
8127 assert(S == MCDisassembler::Fail);
8128 // If the decoding was incomplete, skip.
8129 Ptr += NumToSkip;
8130 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FAIL: continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
8131 // Reset decode status. This also drops a SoftFail status that could be
8132 // set before the decode attempt.
8133 S = MCDisassembler::Success;
8134 }
8135 break;
8136 }
8137 case MCD::OPC_SoftFail: {
8138 // Decode the mask values.
8139 unsigned Len;
8140 InsnType PositiveMask = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
8141 Ptr += Len;
8142 InsnType NegativeMask = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
8143 Ptr += Len;
8144 bool Fail = (insn & PositiveMask) || (~insn & NegativeMask);
8145 if (Fail)
8146 S = MCDisassembler::SoftFail;
8147 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_SoftFail: " << (Fail ? "FAIL\n" : "PASS\n"));
8148 break;
8149 }
8150 case MCD::OPC_Fail: {
8151 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Fail\n");
8152 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
8153 }
8154 }
8155 }
8156 llvm_unreachable("bogosity detected in disassembler state machine!");
8157}
